a .vim configuration by jh@jameshome.com

Featuring:

  birdsofparadise.vim
  a faithful and complete vim colorscheme based on Joe Bergantine's 
  spectacular Birds of Paradise theme:
    http://joebergantine.com/werkstatt/birds-of-paradise

  See it here:
    http://jameshome.com/~jh/birdsofparadise.png

  Get it here:
    https://github.com/jameshome/dotvim/blob/master/colors/birdsofparadise.vim

Installation:

  git clone git://github.com/jameshome/dotvim.git ~/.vim

  Symlink .vimrc:

    ln -s ~/.vim/vimrc ~/.vimrc

  Vim plugins are installed as git submodules. Check these out by running:

    cd ~/.vim
    git submodule init
    git submodule update

  Add new ones with:

    git submodule add (git url) bundle/(bundle name)
    git add .

Not in love with your coding font? Try Droid Sans Mono:
  
  http://code.google.com/webfonts/family?family=Droid+Sans+Mono

